<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-29-0241 </DOCNO><TEXT>A potential economic advantage to be gained by placing movable primarycrushers in the pits of open cast mines have been the subject of increasingdiscussions in the industry in the recent months. Furthermore, industryhas already accepted that, to be competitive they must find alternatesin reducing haulage costs. They are looking for economical alternativesto reduce reliance on expensive diesel fuel and to increase efficiency.The potential for marked improvement in overall mining costs, using mobileand semi-mobile in-pit crushers with crushed materials being transportedout of the pit, underground or open-cast, by high angle belt conveyorsis discussed.</TEXT></DOC>